Maritime Central Airways Flight 315 was an international charter flight from London, England to Toronto, Ontario with refueling stops in Reykjav√≠k, Iceland and Goose Bay, Newfoundland. On August 11, 1957, the aircraft operating this flight, a Douglas DC-4, crashed in bad weather near Issoudun, Quebec, killing all 79 people on board. At the time, it was the deadliest aviation accident in Canadian history, and is currently the fifth-deadliest as of 2016.
